--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation Instructions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


1) Install GPT


Make sure that the variable GPTLICENSE is set to your GPT license number.


2) Install Bmad

Install instructions and source code can be found on the Bmad website:
https://www.classe.cornell.edu/~dcs/bmad/

Additionally, add the following line to your ~/.bashrc file (~/.bash_profile
if you are on a mac):
export PATH="$PATH:$DIST_BASE_DIR/debug/bin:$DIST_BASE_DIR/production/bin"

3) Run the Install Script

Change to the fullbeamline directory and run 'sudo python3 setup.py install'

4) Check the Installation

Run 'source ~/.bashrc' (change ~/.bashrc to ~/.bash_profile if you are on a mac)
to ensure your environment variables are up to date, and then run
'fullbeamline --check'. This should either print 'ok', or give an error message
with instructions.

5) Build Bmad

Run 'fullbeamline --build debug' or 'fullbeamline --build production' to rebuild
Bmad with custom code.
